715737f-b.title: Manhattan: 165th Street (West) - Fort Washington Avenue
715737f-b.text:
(1)
West 165th Street, south side, east from Fort Washington Ave., to
and including Broadway. The corner house (foreground) bears Nos. 130-
142 on Fort Washington Ave. and the others Nos. 626 to 600 on West 165th
Street. Also shown (left) is excavation work on the foundation for the
Eye Institute, a unit of Columbia-Presbyterian Medical Centre, at the
N.E. corner of West 165th Street and Fort Washington Ave.
September 29, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, a more limited view, and showing the east side of Fort
Washington Ave., south from West 165th Street.
September 29, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

715740f-a.title: Manhattan: 165th Street (West) - Fort Washington Avenue
715740f-a.text:
West 165th Street, south side, west from Fort Washington Ave., across
Riverside Drive to the North (Hudson) River, showing the northern side of
the grounds of the New York Institution for the Deaf. Prominent structure
at the S.W. corner of Fort Washington Ave. and West 165th Street is the
Vocational School.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
715740f-a.folder: 165th Street (West) & Fort Washington Avenue, Manhattan, NY

715741f-a.title: Manhattan: 165th Street (West) - Fort Washington Avenue
715741f-a.text:
West 165th Street, north side, west from Fort Washington Ave., across
R(iverside Drive to the North (Hudson) River and showing across the latter
the Jersey highlands and the George Washington Bridge. The property
on the right is a part of the Columbia University-Presbyterian Medical
Center and partially shown thereon is the Presbyterian Hospital School
of Nursing.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
715741f-a.folder: 165th Street (West) & Fort Washington Avenue, Manhattan, NY

719817f-b.title: Manhattan: Fort Washington Aven - 165th Street (West)
719817f-b.text:
Port Washington Ave., west side, south from West 165th Street, show-
ing the rear of the grounds of the New York Institution for the Deaf.
On the right appears the Vocational.School. No. 2 of this set is from
a vantage point at 164th Street and shows another unit, this being at
the N.W. corner of 16inA Street.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

719821f-a.title: Manhattan: Fort Washington Aven - 165th Street (West)
719821f-a.text:
Fort Washington Ave., north from West 165th Street and showing
prominently on the west side of same two units of Columbia University-
Presbyterian Medical Center; the Presbyterian Hospital School of Nursing
and the Neurological Institute. The latter is the center structure.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

719820f-b.title: Manhattan: Fort Washington Aven - 165th Street (West)
719820f-b.text:
(1)
Fort Washington Ave., at the N.W. corner of West 165th Street, show-
ing across rocks at that point, units of Cornell University-Presbyterian
Hospital Center.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A similar view at an earlier date, as photographed in a northwestward
direction from West 165th Street (foreground), slightly east of Fort
Washington Ave. (center). Note at the right, several of the buildings
that were replaced by the Neurological Institute as seen in No. 1. The
prominent building appearing in both views is the Presbyterian Hospital
School of Nursin2.
November 9, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
